ruby-wx
------------------------------------------
wxRuby is an open source GUI toolkit for the Ruby programming 
language. It allows native-looking desktop applications to be written 
for Windows, OS X, Linux GTK and other platforms using only Ruby. It's 
based on the cross-platform wxWidgets C++ GUI framework.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.0-60
  libgcc1-4.3.2-2
  libstdc++6-4.3.2-2
  libwx_baseu2.8_0-2.8.10.1-1
  libwx_gtk2u2.8_0-2.8.10.1-1
  ruby-1.8.7_p72-10

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.19.51-1
  cygport-0.9.9-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.2-2
  gcc4-g++-4.3.2-2
  rake-0.8.4-1
  swig-1.3.38-1

Canonical website:
  http://wxruby.rubyforge.org/wiki/wiki.pl

Canonical download:
  http://rubyforge.org/projects/wxruby/files

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack ruby-wx-2.0.1-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./ruby-wx-2.0.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/ruby-wx-2.0.1-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/ruby-wx-2.0.1-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

